    <text id="B0062T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Keiser asks Jackson to help him to evict three hired people whose term is up.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr Th. P. Jackson</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-02-20"><abbr expan="February">Feby</abbr> 20th 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Waynesboro</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You did not come on tuesday as you promised me. Those negroes are still in <orig
                        reg="there">their</orig> and want possession of the house. As I told I gave
                    them 3 weeks notice one I hired only by the week and settle up with her the
                    other one has been staying <orig reg="there">their</orig> she has good
                    opportunities to hire for more than I gave her but she thinks I think that <orig
                        reg="they">the</orig> will draw a support from the government but she is
                    able support herself you will <orig reg="accomodate">accomdate</orig> me by
                    removing them immediately and you oblige </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>yours &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>John K. Keiser</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
